Introduction
============

This script is written by PERL, and it doesn't rely on other software and modules.
You can download PERL from https://www.perl.org/

Function
========

Batch translation of DNA sequences into protein sequences by using the six-frame translation method.

Usage
=====

perl dna_to_protein.pl <dna_fasta_file>

explain
=======

X indicates any amino acid, and * indicates stop codon (you can modify it on line 16 of the script).

notice
======

Except for the beginning, character > can't appear in the sequence name.

output
======

A DNA sequence produces six protein sequences, + and - indicates positive and negative strand respectively.
